;b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://wpdeveloper.net/?p=270020\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:383:\"<p>Gutenberg Keyboard Shortcuts cover a wide are, ranging from Text Formatting to Block specific commands.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/wordpress-gutenberg-keyboard-shortcuts/\">Use WordPress Gutenberg Keyboard Shortcuts Like a Pro To Increase Productivity</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpdeveloper.net\">WPDeveloper</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Editorial Staff\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6719:\"<p>Shortcuts make life simpler. Gutenberg is no different. It has a wide array of <strong><a href=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/import-gutenberg-blocks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Gutenberg keyboard shortcuts</a></strong>, ranging from Text Formatting to Block specific commands. Just imagine the amount of time you can save if you could accomplish certain tasks with a few button presses instead of a few mouse clicks. Once you know Key-board shortcuts to the most commonly used commands, you no longer have to take your fingers off the keyboard.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-270020\"></span></p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-303065 size-full\" src=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Gutenberg-keyboard-shortcuts-to-use-like-a-pro.png\" alt=\"Gutenberg Keyboard Shortcuts \" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" srcset=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Gutenberg-keyboard-shortcuts-to-use-like-a-pro.png 1280w, https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Gutenberg-keyboard-shortcuts-to-use-like-a-pro-600x338.png 600w, https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Gutenberg-keyboard-shortcuts-to-use-like-a-pro-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/gutenberg/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Gutenberg</strong></a> has been around for a long time now. If you have been using Gutenberg, its time to game up your performance by learning some quick shortcuts that you can us every day for increased productivity.</p>\n<h3>Gutenberg Keyboard Shortcuts</h3>\n<p><strong>Redo and Undo-</strong> Almost on all Desktop Application, <strong>&#8220;Ctrl+Z&#8221;</strong> is used to Undo the last changes you made. This key is also applicable for Gutenberg Editor. However, the exact opposite command, &#8220;Redo&#8221;, can not be performed using the shortcut <strong>&#8220;Ctlr+Y&#8221;</strong>. In order to Redo a certain task, you have to press the buttons. <strong>&#8220;Ctrl+Shift+Z&#8221;</strong></p>\n<p>The Redo and Undo shortcuts are part of the Global shortcuts bundle, which includes another 10 short-cuts.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-270027\" src=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WPDeveloper-Global-Shortcuts.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"454\" srcset=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WPDeveloper-Global-Shortcuts.png 450w, https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WPDeveloper-Global-Shortcuts-100x100.png 100w, https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WPDeveloper-Global-Shortcuts-128x128.png 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Copy and Paste- </strong>When you are in Gutenberg Editor, it is not possible to copy certain blocks and paste them like you would do within the Classic WordPress Editor. In order to copy something, you need to duplicate that block, use the keys <strong>&#8220;Ctrl+Shift+D&#8221; </strong>to duplicate a certain block.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-270028\" src=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WPDeveloper-Block-Shortcuts.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"449\" height=\"210\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Text Formatting-</strong> The basic Text Formatting commands are similar to other Text Editors such as Microsoft Word, Google Docs as well as the old WordPress Classic Editor. Press<strong> &#8220;Ctrl+B&#8221;</strong> for bold formatting, press <strong>&#8220;Ctrl+I&#8221;</strong> for italic formatting, press <strong>&#8220;Ctrl+U&#8221;</strong> for underline formatting.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-270029\" src=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WPDeveloper-Text-Formatting.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"452\" height=\"283\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Adding and Removing Links- </strong>In order to convert a selected text into a link press the keys <strong>&#8220;Ctrl+K&#8221;. </strong>To do the exact opposite, simply add a Shift stroke in the middle <strong>&#8220;Ctrl+Shift+K&#8221;.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Show or Hide the Settings Sidebar-</strong>Inside the Gutenberg Editor, the sidebar plays a big role. It contains all the settings and customization options for individual blocks as well as the overall web page. But in case you feel overwhelmed by its appearance, you can hide it when you don\'t require it. To hide the Sidebar press the keys <strong>&#8220;Ctrl+Shift+,&#8221;</strong></p>\n<p>Luckily you don\'t need to memorize all these Gutenberg keyboard shortcuts. Why? Because you will have them right in front of you as soon as you press <strong>&#8220;Shift+Alt+H&#8221; </strong>inside the Gutenberg Editor.</p>\n<h2> Bonus: Boost Your Gutenberg Experience with Ready Templates for Gutenberg [FREE]</h2>\n<p>As Gutenberg Editor is getting popular these days, so we want to help people to make their web building experience better with advanced Gutenberg Addons &#8211; <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/essential-blocks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Essential Block for Gutenberg</a>. It comes with 23+ blocks to power up Gutenberg editor.</p>\n<p>But that\'s not just it! We\'ve also introduced <strong><a href=\"https://templately.com/all\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Templately</a></strong>&#8211; the ultimate template clouds for Gutenberg Editor & Elementor Page Builder. It brings hundreds of ready WordPress templates and you can use cloud storage to re-use the blocks and <a href=\"https://essential-addons.com/elementor/templately-workspace-elementor/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">collaborate with your team member on the cloud.</a></p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-472778 size-full\" src=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screen-Shot-on-2020-05-31-at-15-43-10.png\" alt=\"Gutenberg block templates\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1284\" srcset=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screen-Shot-on-2020-05-31-at-15-43-10.png 2048w, https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screen-Shot-on-2020-05-31-at-15-43-10-600x376.png 600w, https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screen-Shot-on-2020-05-31-at-15-43-10-1600x1003.png 1600w, https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screen-Shot-on-2020-05-31-at-15-43-10-768x481.png 768w, https://wpdeveloper.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screen-Shot-on-2020-05-31-at-15-43-10-1536x963.png 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2048px) 100vw, 2048px\" /></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpdeveloper.net/wordpress-gutenberg-keyboard-shortcuts/\">Use WordPress Gutenberg Keyboard Shortcuts Like a Pro To Increase Productivity</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpdeveloper.net\">WPDeveloper</a>.</p>\n